<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4927] KStreamsTestDriver fails with NPE when KStream.to() sinks are used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4927</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Context&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
KStreamsTestDriver allows to build integration tests of KStreamsTopologies. This also includes topologies that sink data into outgoing topics by calling the KStream.to() methods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Problem&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
When a topic is added as a sink, the KStreamsTestDriver fails with NullPointerExceptions. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Solution&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
BugFix the method KStreamTestDriver.process() method to also lookup a topic  by topicName as a sink when a source has not been found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;PullRequest&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
